About
Today’s menu has come a long way from it’s very humble beginnings in June 1987
                as one of the original tenants of the Jacksonville Landing.
Today’s menu has come a long way from it’s very humble beginnings in June 1987
                as one of the original tenants of the Jacksonville Landing.
VIEW MENU
THE AUTHENTIC FLAVORS OF NEW ORLEANS
Founded by Louis and Greg Saig, the original store had about 20 stools and a very
                limited raw bar menu. It was by chance that our first menu items were influenced by a couple fellas from
                Louisiana. These bold flavors and unique ingredients made a lasting impression on the development of the
                menu that you still see today.
Louis and partner Jesse Jabot along with an incredible corporate team, general
                managers, managers and staff at every level; strive toward always providing quality food and impeccable
                service all at a great value.
Our mission at Harry's is to earn our guest's and our employee's loyalty by
                creating raving fans. This has remained the same since we opened back in 1987.
We've adopted a couple expressions commonly used in Louisiana as part of our culture. The first is
            "Lagniappe" (pronounced lan-yap) which means "to give a little something extra". We believe our customers
            deserve that little extra effort that take an ordinary experience to extraordinary.
The second is "Laissez Les Bon Temps Rouler"
"Let the Good Times Roll".
